title: Aruba Switch 6100+ series: Temperature
agents: snmp
catalog: hw/network/aruba
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the temperature of Aruba 6100+ devices.

 For these devices, different temperature thresholds are defined for the different sensors, i.e.,

 - CPU / ASIC / PHY: 80°C (WARN), 90°C (CRIT)
 - DDR: 60°C (WARN), 70°C (CRIT)
 - PCIE: 55°C (WARN), 60°C (CRIT)
 - IBC: 45°C (WARN), 50°C (CRIT)
 - Exhaust: 45°C (WARN), 50°C (CRIT)
 - Internal: 45°C (WARN), 50°C (CRIT)
 - DDR Inlet: 40°C (WARN), 45°C (CRIT)
 - Inlet: 30°C (WARN), 40°C (CRIT)
 - Board-rear: 45°C (WARN), 50°C (CRIT)
 - Mainboard and Default (Board-front, Board-NW, Board-W, etc.): 35°C (WARN), 40°C (CRIT)

 When a sensor is in a "fault" state, this check is in a "WARN" state.
 When the sensor is in the "emergency" state, the check is in the "CRIT" state.

 The check uses the arubaWiredTempSensorEntry-MIB.

item:
 The sensor name.

discovery:
 One service is created for each temperature sensor. Sensors with the state 'absent' will not be discovered.
